The paper deals with efficient point location in the SINR diagram, which is a geometric structure. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes data structures and algorithms for answering batched point location queries, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The SINR model is related to information theory, which is covered in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the sensitivity of reception regions to changes in reception threshold, which is related to numerical analysis and optimization, covered in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
